# README Formatting Rules

## Overview

This rule defines the preferred formatting style for README.md files. Use this style when creating or editing README documentation.

---

## Structure Guidelines

### 1. Start with a Short Overview Section

Every README should begin with a brief overview section that:
- Provides a concise 2-3 sentence description of the project/script
- Explains what the code does and why it's useful
- Sets context for readers

